Noun

Neologism to describe an individual working in a low paid job service industry position using information technologies. The individuals have usually only attained a basic qualification and so are not in position to use their knowledge to move on to a higher paid position.

Derivation:

"[[Micro]]" from the company name "Microsoft" due to the ubiqitous use of the company's products.
"[[Serf]]" slavic term for an indentured labourer.

See also [[McJob]]